              "prepNote": "for the white icing glaze",
              "quantity": 150,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientSlug": "icing-sugar"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientItem",
            "attrs": {
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": "melted, for the feather decoration",
              "quantity": 30,
              "isOptional": false,
              "ingredientSlug": "dark-chocolate"
            }
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the rough puff and bake the sheets",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Mix the pastry-quantity {{plain-flour}} and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Add the very cold pastry-quantity {{unsalted-butter}} in rough 1 cm pieces and toss briefly in the flour.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Add 80 to 90 ml of ice-cold water and mix to a rough dough with visible butter pieces. Roll to a rectangle, fold in thirds, rotate, and roll again. Repeat twice. Wrap and refrigerate for 60 minutes.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan (220°C conventional). Roll the chilled pastry to a rectangle about 3 mm thick and cut into three equal strips of identical size. Place on lined baking trays.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bake for 12 minutes, then lay a sheet of baking paper over the pastry and press down firmly with a second tray to flatten. Return to the oven for 10 to 12 minutes more until deeply golden and crisp throughout. Cool completely on a rack.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pastry cream",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bring {{whole-milk}} and the seeds and pod from {{vanilla-pod}} to a gentle simmer. Whisk {{egg-yolks}}, {{caster-sugar}}, and the pastry cream-quantity {{plain-flour}} together in a bowl until smooth.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Pour the hot milk over the egg mixture, whisking constantly, then return to the pan. Cook over medium heat, stirring continuously, until the cream thickens and boils for 1 to 2 minutes.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Remove from the heat and stir in the pastry cream-quantity {{unsalted-butter}}. Remove the vanilla pod. Press cling film directly onto the surface and refrigerate until cold and firm, at least 90 minutes.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assemble and ice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Beat the chilled pastry cream to loosen it. Spread or pipe half the cream evenly over one pastry sheet. Place the second sheet on top and spread the remaining cream over it. Place the third sheet on top, pressing gently.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Mix {{icing-sugar}} with enough cold water (about 2 to 3 tablespoons) to make a thick, spreadable icing. Spread evenly over the top sheet.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Pipe lines of melted {{dark-chocolate}} across the icing at 1 cm intervals. Drag a skewer or knife tip across the chocolate lines alternately in opposite directions to create the feather pattern.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Refrigerate for 30 minutes to set. Trim the edges with a sharp serrated knife and slice.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Notes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "A serrated bread knife cuts mille-feuille without compressing the layers. Saw gently rather than pressing straight down.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "For a raspberry mille-feuille: fold 150 g of fresh raspberries into the pastry cream before assembling, and scatter a few on top of the cream layers.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "The pastry cream can be made up to two days ahead. Whisk briskly before using if it has set very firm in the fridge.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
